productType.name: productType

productVersion.name: productVersion
productVersion.description: Version String for the Software Running on this platform.

productId.name: productId
productId.description: The System ID of this system.

productVendor.name: productVendor
productVendor.description: The vendor id of this system, indicating the company that has supplied the product.

productModel.name: productModel
productModel.description: The model name of the system. Examples are FAS980 and FAS3050.

productFirmwareVersion.name: productFirmwareVersion
productFirmwareVersion.description: Version string for the Firmware running on this platform.

productGuiUrl.name: productGuiUrl
productGuiUrl.description: The complete URL used to access the administrative GUI for a browser-based interface.

productApiUrl.name: productApiUrl
productApiUrl.description: The complete URL used to access the administrative API for a programmatic interface.

productSerialNum.name: productSerialNum
productSerialNum.description: The product serial number. Returns unknown if it cannot be determined.

productPartnerSerialNum.name: productPartnerSerialNum
productPartnerSerialNum.description: The partner's serial number, not applicable if there is no partner, and unknown if it cannot be determined.

productCPUArch.name: productCPUArch
productCPUArch.description: The CPU architecture type of this appliance

productTrapData.name: productTrapData
productTrapData.description: This returns a static string. This object is used as a placeholder for enterprise traps.

productMachineType.name: productMachineType
productMachineType.description: The machine type of the system. Examples are FAS980 and FAS3050.

cpuUpTime.name: cpuUpTime
cpuUpTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) that the CPU has been up since the last boot.

cpuBusyTime.name: cpuBusyTime
cpuBusyTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) that the CPU has been doing useful work since the last boot.

cpuBusyTimePerCent.name: cpuBusyTimePerCent
cpuBusyTimePerCent.description: The percent of time that the CPU has been doing useful work since the last time a client requested the cpuBusyTimePerCent.

cpuIdleTime.name: cpuIdleTime
cpuIdleTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) that the CPU has been idle since the last boot.

cpuIdleTimePerCent.name: cpuIdleTimePerCent
cpuIdleTimePerCent.description: The percent of time that the CPU has been idle since the last time a client requested the cpuBusyTimePerCent.

cpuCount.name: cpuCount
cpuCount.description: The number of CPUs in the system.

cpuContextSwitches.name: cpuContextSwitches
cpuContextSwitches.description: The number of hardware context switches.

cpuInterrupts.name: cpuInterrupts
cpuInterrupts.description: The number of interrupts during a CP.

cpuNonCPInterrupts.name: cpuNonCPInterrupts
cpuNonCPInterrupts.description: The number of interrupts not during a CP.

cpuCPInterruptPercent.name: cpuCPInterruptPercent
cpuCPInterruptPercent.description: The percentage of time handling CP interrupts.

cpuNonCPInterruptPercent.name: cpuNonCPInterruptPercent
cpuNonCPInterruptPercent.description: The percentage of time handling non-cp interrupts.

cpuTotalDomainSwitches.name: cpuTotalDomainSwitches
cpuTotalDomainSwitches.description: The total number of Domain Switches.

miscNfsOps.name: miscNfsOps
miscNfsOps.description: The total number of Server side NFS calls since the last boot

miscNetRcvdKB.name: miscNetRcvdKB
miscNetRcvdKB.description: The total number of KBytes received on all the network interfaces, since the last boot.

miscNetSentKB.name: miscNetSentKB
miscNetSentKB.description: The total number of KBytes transmitted on all the network interfaces, since the last boot.

miscGlobalStatus.name: miscGlobalStatus
miscGlobalStatus.description: This indicates the overall status of the appliance. The algorithm to determine the value uses both hardware status (e.g. the number of failed fans) and volume status (e.g. number of volumes that are full). The algorithm is subject to change in future releases, but the range of values will not change.

miscHighNfsOps.name: miscHighNfsOps
miscHighNfsOps.description: The total number of Server side NFS calls since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

miscLowNfsOps.name: miscLowNfsOps
miscLowNfsOps.description: The total number of Server side NFS calls since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

miscHighCifsOps.name: miscHighCifsOps
miscHighCifsOps.description: The total number of Server side CIFS calls since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

miscLowCifsOps.name: miscLowCifsOps
miscLowCifsOps.description: The total number of Server side CIFS calls since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

miscHighHttpOps.name: miscHighHttpOps
miscHighHttpOps.description: The total number of HTTP operations received since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

miscLowHttpOps.name: miscLowHttpOps
miscLowHttpOps.description: The total number of HTTP operations received since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

miscHighNetRcvdBytes.name: miscHighNetRcvdBytes

miscLowNetRcvdBytes.name: miscLowNetRcvdBytes

miscLowNetSentBytes.name: miscLowNetSentBytes

miscLowDiskReadBytes.name: miscLowDiskReadBytes

miscHighDiskWriteBytes.name: miscHighDiskWriteBytes
miscHighDiskWriteBytes.description: The total number of bytes written to disk since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

miscLowDiskWriteBytes.name: miscLowDiskWriteBytes
miscLowDiskWriteBytes.description: The total number of bytes written to disk since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

miscHighTapeReadBytes.name: miscHighTapeReadBytes
miscHighTapeReadBytes.description: The total number of bytes read from tape since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

miscLowTapeReadBytes.name: miscLowTapeReadBytes
miscLowTapeReadBytes.description: The total number of bytes read from tape since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

miscHighTapeWriteBytes.name: miscHighTapeWriteBytes
miscHighTapeWriteBytes.description: The total number of bytes written to tape since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

miscLowTapeWriteBytes.name: miscLowTapeWriteBytes
miscLowTapeWriteBytes.description: The total number of bytes written to tape since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

miscCacheAge.name: miscCacheAge
miscCacheAge.description: Age in minutes of the oldest read-only blocks in the buffer cache. This indicates how fast read operations are cycling through system memory; when the appliance is reading very large files (larger than the machine's memory size), buffer cache age will be very low.

miscCorrectedMachineChecks.name: miscCorrectedMachineChecks
miscCorrectedMachineChecks.description: Number of corrected machine checks since the last boot.

miscGlobalStatusMessage.name: miscGlobalStatusMessage
miscGlobalStatusMessage.description: A string describing the global status, including a description of the condition (if any) that caused the status to be anything other than ok(3).

miscWindowsSetupWizardVersion.name: miscWindowsSetupWizardVersion
miscWindowsSetupWizardVersion.description: The version number of Windows Setup Wizard required to configure the appliance. Windows Setup Wizard with a version number lower than this integer is not capable of configuring the appliance.

misc64NfsOps.name: misc64NfsOps
misc64NfsOps.description: The total number of Server side NFS calls since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

misc64CifsOps.name: misc64CifsOps
misc64CifsOps.description: The total number of Server side CIFS calls since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

misc64HttpOps.name: misc64HttpOps
misc64HttpOps.description: The total number of HTTP operations received since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

misc64NetRcvdBytes.name: misc64NetRcvdBytes
misc64NetRcvdBytes.description: The total number of bytes received on all the network interfaces, since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

misc64NetSentBytes.name: misc64NetSentBytes
misc64NetSentBytes.description: The total number of bytes transmitted on all the network interfaces, since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

misc64DiskReadBytes.name: misc64DiskReadBytes

cfSettings.name: cfSettings
cfSettings.description: Clustered Failover configuration settings. The value notConfigured(1) indicates that the cluster is not licensed. The thisNodeDead(5) setting indicates that this node has been taken over.

cfCannotTakeoverCause.name: cfCannotTakeoverCause
cfCannotTakeoverCause.description: The reason this node cannot takeover its partner

cfPartnerStatus.name: cfPartnerStatus
cfPartnerStatus.description: This is the status last returned by the Clustered Failover partner.

cfPartnerLastStatusUpdate.name: cfPartnerLastStatusUpdate
cfPartnerLastStatusUpdate.description: If non-zero, the absolute time of the last update from the Clustered Failover partner.

cfPartnerSysid.name: cfPartnerSysid
cfPartnerSysid.description: System ID for Clustered Failover partner.

cfInterconnectStatus.name: cfInterconnectStatus
cfInterconnectStatus.description: The current status of the interconnect. The partialFailure(3) status indicates that one of the links in the interconnect hardware is down.

envOverTemperature.name: envOverTemperature
envOverTemperature.description: An indication of whether the hardware is currently operating outside of its recommended temperature range. The hardware will shutdown if the temperature exceeds critical thresholds.

envFailedFanCount.name: envFailedFanCount
envFailedFanCount.description: Count of the number of chassis fans which are not operating within the recommended RPM range.

envFailedFanMessage.name: envFailedFanMessage
envFailedFanMessage.description: Text message describing the current condition of chassis fans. This is useful only if envFailedFanCount is not zero.

envFailedPowerSupplyCount.name: envFailedPowerSupplyCount
envFailedPowerSupplyCount.description: Count of the number of power supplies which are in degraded mode.

envFailedPowerSupplyMessage.name: envFailedPowerSupplyMessage
envFailedPowerSupplyMessage.description: Text message describing the state of any power supplies which are currently degraded. This is useful only if envFailedPowerSupplyCount is not zero.

nvramBatteryStatus.name: nvramBatteryStatus
nvramBatteryStatus.description: An indication of the current status of the NVRAM battery or batteries. Batteries which are fully or partially discharged may not fully protect the system during a crash. The end-of-life status values are based on the manufacturer's recommended life for the batteries.

cpTime.name: cpTime
cpTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since boot during which the system has had a consistency point (cp) operation in progress.

cpFromTimerOps.name: cpFromTimerOps
cpFromTimerOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by timer.

cpFromSnapshotOps.name: cpFromSnapshotOps
cpFromSnapshotOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by snapshot operation.

cpFromLowWaterOps.name: cpFromLowWaterOps
cpFromLowWaterOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by low water mark.

cpFromHighWaterOps.name: cpFromHighWaterOps
cpFromHighWaterOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by high water mark.

cpFromLogFullOps.name: cpFromLogFullOps
cpFromLogFullOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by nv-log full.

cpFromCpOps.name: cpFromCpOps
cpFromCpOps.description: The number of back to back consistency point operations since boot.

cpTotalOps.name: cpTotalOps
cpTotalOps.description: The total number of consistency point operations since boot.

cpFromFlushOps.name: cpFromFlushOps
cpFromFlushOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by flushing unlogged write data.

cpFromSyncOps.name: cpFromSyncOps
cpFromSyncOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by file system sync requests.

cpFromLowVbufOps.name: cpFromLowVbufOps
cpFromLowVbufOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by low virtual buffers.

cpFromCpDeferredOps.name: cpFromCpDeferredOps
cpFromCpDeferredOps.description: The number of back to back consistency point operations since boot that were deferred.

cpFromLowDatavecsOps.name: cpFromLowDatavecsOps
cpFromLowDatavecsOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by low datavecs.

autosupportStatus.name: autosupportStatus
autosupportStatus.description: An indication of the current status of autosupport on the appliance. describes the success or failure of most recent attempts to send autosupports.

autosupportStatusMessage.name: autosupportStatusMessage
autosupportStatusMessage.description: A string describing the autosupport status, including a description of the condition (if any) that caused the status to be anything other than ok(1).

autosupportSuccessfulSends.name: autosupportSuccessfulSends
autosupportSuccessfulSends.description: Count of the number of autosupport messages successfully sent since the last reset.

autosupportFailedSends.name: autosupportFailedSends
autosupportFailedSends.description: Count of the number of autosupport messages not sent successfully since the last reset.

rpcCalls.name: rpcCalls
rpcCalls.description: The total number of RPC calls received, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

rpcBadCalls.name: rpcBadCalls
rpcBadCalls.description: The total number of calls rejected by the RPC layer, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

rpcNullRecvs.name: rpcNullRecvs
rpcNullRecvs.description: The number of times an RPC call was not available when it was thought to be received, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

rpcBadLens.name: rpcBadLens
rpcBadLens.description: The number of RPC calls received with a length shorter than a minimum-sized RPC call, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

rpcServXDRCalls.name: rpcServXDRCalls
rpcServXDRCalls.description: The number of RPC calls received whose header could not be XDR decoded, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

rcpTcpCalls.name: rcpTcpCalls
rcpTcpCalls.description: The total number of RPC calls received for the TCP protocol, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

rcpTcpBadLens.name: rcpTcpBadLens

rcpTcpServXDRCalls.name: rcpTcpServXDRCalls
rcpTcpServXDRCalls.description: The number of RPC calls for the TCP protocol received whose header could not be XDR decoded, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

rpcUdpCalls.name: rpcUdpCalls
rpcUdpCalls.description: The total number of RPC calls received for the UDP protocol, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

rpcUdpBadCalls.description: The total number of calls rejected by the RPC layer for the UDP protocol, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

rpcUdpNullRecvs.name: rpcUdpNullRecvs

rpcUdpBadLens.name: rpcUdpBadLens
rpcUdpBadLens.description: The number of RPC calls for the UDP protocol received with a length shorter than a minimum-sized RPC call, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

rpcUdpServXDRCalls.name: rpcUdpServXDRCalls

rcInProgressHits.name: rcInProgressHits
rcInProgressHits.description: The number of NFS requests that were dropped, for calls already in progress, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

rcDelayHits.name: rcDelayHits
rcDelayHits.description: The number of NFS requests that were dropped, for replies already generated within a short interval, since the last time the statistics were cleared. These stats are deprecated. A value of zero will always be returned for these stats.

rcMisses.name: rcMisses
rcMisses.description: The number of NFS requests received for which there were no corresponding entries already in the Reply Cache, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

rcNonIdemDoneHits.name: rcNonIdemDoneHits

rcNonIdemNotDoneHits.name: rcNonIdemNotDoneHits

rcTcpInProgressHits.name: rcTcpInProgressHits

pclTable.name: pclTable
pclTable.description: Provide a report of per-client NFS statistics since the last time the statistics were cleared.

pclEntry.name: pclEntry
pclEntry.description: Provide a report of NFS statistics for the referenced NFS client since the last time the statistics were cleared.

pclIpAddr.name: pclIpAddr
pclIpAddr.description: The IP address of the referenced client.

pclRpcCalls.name: pclRpcCalls
pclRpcCalls.description: The total number of RPC calls received from the referenced client, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

pclRpcBadCalls.name: pclRpcBadCalls
pclRpcBadCalls.description: The total number of calls received from the referenced client that were rejected by the RPC layer, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

pclRpcNullRecvs.name: pclRpcNullRecvs
pclRpcNullRecvs.description: The number of times an RPC call was not available when it was thought to be received from referenced client, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

pclRpcBadLens.name: pclRpcBadLens
pclRpcBadLens.description: The number of RPC calls received from the referenced client with a length shorter than a minimum-sized RPC call, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

pclRpcServXDRCalls.name: pclRpcServXDRCalls
pclRpcServXDRCalls.description: The number of RPC calls received from the referenced client whose header could not be XDR decoded, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

pclNfsCalls.name: pclNfsCalls
pclNfsCalls.description: The total number of NFS calls received from the referenced client, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

pclNfsServBadCalls.name: pclNfsServBadCalls
pclNfsServBadCalls.description: The total number of NFS calls received from the referenced client that were rejected, since the last time the statistics were cleared.

tv3cpPathconfs.description: The number of NFS Version 3 calls received for the NFSPROC3_PATHCONF (Retrieve POSIX Information) procedure, that did not result in the filesystem blocking to read from disk, as a percentage of the total number of calls received for this procedure, since the last boot.

tv3cpCommits.name: tv3cpCommits
tv3cpCommits.description: The number of NFS Version 3 calls received for the NFSPROC3_COMMIT (Commit Cached Data on a Server to Stable Storage) procedure, that did not result in the filesystem blocking to read from disk, as a percentage of the total number of calls received for this procedure, since the last boot.

trcInProgressHits.name: trcInProgressHits
trcInProgressHits.description: The number of NFS requests that were dropped, for calls already in progress, since the last boot.

trcDelayHits.name: trcDelayHits
trcDelayHits.description: The number of NFS requests that were dropped, for replies already generated within a short interval, since the last boot. These stats are deprecated. A value of zero will always be returned for these stats.

trcMisses.name: trcMisses
trcMisses.description: The number of NFS requests received for which there were no corresponding entries already in the Reply Cache, since the last boot.

trcNonIdemDoneHits.name: trcNonIdemDoneHits
trcNonIdemDoneHits.description: The number of NFS requests received that resulted in replies being replayed from the Reply Cache, since the last boot.

trcNonIdemNotDoneHits.name: trcNonIdemNotDoneHits
trcNonIdemNotDoneHits.description: The number of NFS requests received for calls that resulted in this request being processed as a new request even when a corresponding entry existed in the Reply Cache, since the last boot.

trcTcpInProgressHits.name: trcTcpInProgressHits
trcTcpInProgressHits.description: The number of NFS requests that were dropped for the TCP protocol, for calls already in progress, since the last boot.

trcTcpDelayHits.name: trcTcpDelayHits
trcTcpDelayHits.description: The number of NFS requests that were dropped for the TCP protocol, for replies already generated within a short interval, since the last boot. These stats are deprecated. A value of zero will always be returned for these stats.

trcTcpMisses.name: trcTcpMisses
trcTcpMisses.description: The number of NFS requests received for the TCP protocol for which there were no corresponding entries already in the Reply Cache, since the last boot.

trcTcpNonIdemDoneHits.name: trcTcpNonIdemDoneHits
trcTcpNonIdemDoneHits.description: The number of NFS requests received for the TCP protocol that resulted in replies being replayed from the Reply Cache, since the last boot.

trcTcpNonIdemNotDoneHits.name: trcTcpNonIdemNotDoneHits
trcTcpNonIdemNotDoneHits.description: The number of NFS requests received for the TCP protocol for calls that resulted in this request being processed as a new request even when a corresponding entry existed in the Reply Cache, since the last boot.

trcUdpInProgressHits.name: trcUdpInProgressHits
trcUdpInProgressHits.description: The number of NFS requests that were dropped for the UDP protocol, for calls already in progress, since the last boot.

trcUdpDelayHits.name: trcUdpDelayHits
trcUdpDelayHits.description: The number of NFS requests that were dropped for the UDP protocol, for replies already generated within a short interval, since the last boot. These stats are deprecated. A value of zero will always be returned for these stats.

trcUdpMisses.name: trcUdpMisses
trcUdpMisses.description: The number of NFS requests received for the UDP protocol for which there were no corresponding entries already in the Reply Cache, since the last boot.

trcUdpNonIdemDoneHits.name: trcUdpNonIdemDoneHits
trcUdpNonIdemDoneHits.description: The number of NFS requests received for the UDP protocol that resulted in replies being replayed from the Reply Cache, since the last boot.

trcUdpNonIdemNotDoneHits.name: trcUdpNonIdemNotDoneHits
trcUdpNonIdemNotDoneHits.description: The number of NFS requests received for the UDP protocol for calls that resulted in this request being processed as a new request even when a corresponding entry existed in the Reply Cache, since the last boot.

nfsIsLicensed.name: nfsIsLicensed
nfsIsLicensed.description: Whether the nfs protocol is licensed on the filer.

quotaState.name: quotaState
quotaState.description: Indicates whether the root volume's quotas are ON, OFF or initializing. This object is deprecated - use qvStateTable.qvStateStat instead.

quotaInitPercent.name: quotaInitPercent
quotaInitPercent.description: Indicates percentage of root volume quota computation done while quotas are in initializing state. This object is deprecated - use qvStateTable.qvInitPercent instead.

qrTable.name: qrTable
qrTable.description: Provide a report of the current file and space consumption for each user or group with a quota in /etc/quotas. All quotas are displayed regardless of volume, and no volume information is given. This table is deprecated - use qrVTable instead.

qrEntry.name: qrEntry
qrEntry.description: Provide a report of the current file and space consumption for a referenced entry with a quota in the file /etc/quotas. All quotas are displayed regardless of volume, and no volume information is given. This object is deprecated - use qrVEntry instead.

qrIndex.name: qrIndex
qrIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry in the file /etc/quotas.

qrType.name: qrType
qrType.description: Identifies the kind of quota for this qrEntry.

qrId.name: qrId
qrId.description: The UID (user's numerical ID) or the GID (numerical ID of the group that a user belongs to), as applicable, associated with this qrEntry.

qrKBytesUsed.name: qrKBytesUsed
qrKBytesUsed.description: The current number of KBytes used for this qrEntry.

qrKBytesLimit.name: qrKBytesLimit
qrKBytesLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrEntry.

qrFilesUsed.name: qrFilesUsed
qrFilesUsed.description: The current number of files used for this qrEntry.

qrFileLimit.name: qrFileLimit
qrFileLimit.description: The limit of files that can be used for this qrEntry.

qrPathName.name: qrPathName
qrPathName.description: A textual string that contains the path corresponding to this qrEntry.

qvStateTable.name: qvStateTable
qvStateTable.description: Provide a report of the current quota state of each volume in the system.

qvStateEntry.name: qvStateEntry
qvStateEntry.description: Provide a report of the current quota state of each volume in the system.

qvStateVolume.name: qvStateVolume
qvStateVolume.description: A number that identifies this volume. The mapping of this number to actual volumes may change if volumes are added or deleted. Use qvStateName to unambiguously identify a volume. The mapping established by this object is the same as the mapping of qrVVolume (below) to actual volumes. For instance, if a qvStateVolume value of '5' represents the volume 'vol2', a value of '5' in qrVVolume also represents the volume 'vol2'.

qvStateName.name: qvStateName
qvStateName.description: Indicates the name of this volume.

qvStateStat.name: qvStateStat
qvStateStat.description: Indicates whether quotas are ON, OFF or initializing.

qvStateInitPercent.name: qvStateInitPercent
qvStateInitPercent.description: Indicates percentage of quota computation done while quotas are in initializing state.

qrVTable.name: qrVTable
qrVTable.description: Provide a report of the current file and space consumption for each user or group with a quota in /etc/quotas.

qrVEntry.name: qrVEntry
qrVEntry.description: Provide a report of the current file and space consumption for a referenced entry with a quota in the file /etc/quotas. Indices select the volume of the quota and the quota entry itself.

qrVIndex.name: qrVIndex
qrVIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry in the file /etc/quotas in the given volume.

qrVType.name: qrVType
qrVType.description: Identifies the kind of quota for this qrVEntry.

qrVId.name: qrVId
qrVId.description: The UID (user's numerical ID) or the GID (numerical ID of the group that a user belongs to), as applicable, associated with this qrVEntry. Check the qrVIdType field to see if this field is valid.

qrVKBytesUsed.name: qrVKBytesUsed
qrVKBytesUsed.description: The current number of KBytes used for this qrVEntry.

qrVKBytesLimit.name: qrVKBytesLimit
qrVKBytesLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrVEntry.

qrVFilesUsed.name: qrVFilesUsed
qrVFilesUsed.description: The current number of files used for this qrVEntry.

qrVFileLimit.name: qrVFileLimit
qrVFileLimit.description: The limit of files that can be used for this qrVEntry.

qrVPathName.name: qrVPathName
qrVPathName.description: A textual string that contains the path corresponding to this qrVEntry.

qrVVolume.name: qrVVolume
qrVVolume.description: A number that identifies the volume for which this quota is in effect on. The volume that this value represents can be determined by checking the value of qvStateName (above) with qvStateVolume set to the value found here.

qrVTree.name: qrVTree
qrVTree.description: A string that indicates which qtree this quota belongs to.

qrVIdType.name: qrVIdType
qrVIdType.description: A value that indicates which ID field is valid.

qrVSid.name: qrVSid
qrVSid.description: The one or more IDs associated with this qrVEntry. If the qrVentry is associated with a Windows ID, the text form of the Windows ID (the SID) is here. If the qrVEntry is associated with more than one id, this contains a blank separated list of those IDs. Check the qrVIdType field to see if this field is valid.

qrVKBytesThreshold.name: qrVKBytesThreshold
qrVKBytesThreshold.description: A number of KBytes that when used by this entry produces a warning message.

qrVKBytesLimitSoft.name: qrVKBytesLimitSoft
qrVKBytesLimitSoft.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrVEntry before a warning message and SNMP trap is produced.

qrVFileLimitSoft.name: qrVFileLimitSoft
qrVFileLimitSoft.description: The limit of files that can be used for this qrVEntry before a warning message and SNMP trap is produced.

qrV2Table.name: qrV2Table
qrV2Table.description: Provide a report of the current file and space consumption for each user or group with a quota in /etc/quotas.

qrV2Entry.name: qrV2Entry
qrV2Entry.description: Provide a report of the current file and space consumption for a referenced entry with a quota in the file /etc/quotas. Indices select the volume of the quota and the quota entry itself.

qrV2Index.name: qrV2Index
qrV2Index.description: A number that identifies this entry in the file /etc/quotas in the given volume.

qrV2Type.name: qrV2Type
qrV2Type.description: Identifies the kind of quota for this qrV2Entry.

qrV2Id.name: qrV2Id
qrV2Id.description: The UID (user's numerical ID) or the GID (numerical ID of the group that a user belongs to), as applicable, associated with this qrV2Entry. Check the qrV2IdType field to see if this field is valid.

qrV2HighKBytesUsed.name: qrV2HighKBytesUsed
qrV2HighKBytesUsed.description: The current number of KBytes used for this qrV2Entry. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

qrV2LowKBytesUsed.name: qrV2LowKBytesUsed
qrV2LowKBytesUsed.description: The current number of KBytes used for this qrV2Entry. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

qrV2QuotaUnlimited.name: qrV2QuotaUnlimited
qrV2QuotaUnlimited.description: This flag designates whether or not the size based quota limit for this qrV2Entry is unlimited. If false(1) then qrV2*KBytesLimit OID's are valid, if true(0) then qrV2*KBytesLimit OID's are unused and will return 0.

qrV2HighKBytesLimit.name: qrV2HighKBytesLimit
qrV2HighKBytesLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrV2Entry. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This will return 0 if qrV2QuotaUnlimited is true.

qrV2LowKBytesLimit.name: qrV2LowKBytesLimit
qrV2LowKBytesLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrV2Entry. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This will return 0 if qrV2QuotaUnlimited is true.

qrV2FilesUsed.name: qrV2FilesUsed
qrV2FilesUsed.description: The current number of files used for this qrV2Entry.

qrV2FileQuotaUnlimited.name: qrV2FileQuotaUnlimited
qrV2FileQuotaUnlimited.description: This flag designates whether or not the file based quota limit for this qrV2Entry is unlimited. If false(1) then qrV2FileLimit is valid, if true(0) qrV2FileLimit will return 0.

qrV2FileLimit.name: qrV2FileLimit
qrV2FileLimit.description: The limit of files that can be used for this qrV2Entry.

qrV2PathName.name: qrV2PathName
qrV2PathName.description: A textual string that contains the path corresponding to this qrV2Entry.

qrV2Volume.name: qrV2Volume
qrV2Volume.description: A number that identifies the volume for which this quota is in effect on. The volume that this value represents can be determined by checking the value of qvStateName (above) with qvStateVolume set to the value found here.

qrV2Tree.name: qrV2Tree
qrV2Tree.description: A string that indicates which qtree this quota belongs to.

qrV2IdType.name: qrV2IdType
qrV2IdType.description: A value that indicates which ID field is valid.

qrV2Sid.name: qrV2Sid
qrV2Sid.description: The one or more IDs associated with this qrV2Entry. If the qrV2entry is associated with a Windows ID, the text form of the Windows ID (the SID) is here. If the qrV2Entry is associated with more than one id, this contains a blank separated list of those IDs. Check the qrV2IdType field to see if this field is valid.

qrV2ThresholdUnlimited.name: qrV2ThresholdUnlimited
qrV2ThresholdUnlimited.description: This flag designates whether or not the size based threshold limit for this qrV2Entry is unlimited. If false(1) then qrV2*KBytesThreshold OID's are valid, if true(0) then qrV2*KBytesThreshold OID's are unused and will return 0.

qrV2HighKBytesThreshold.name: qrV2HighKBytesThreshold
qrV2HighKBytesThreshold.description: A number of KBytes that when used by this entry produces a warning message. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This will return 0 if qrV2ThresholdUnlimited is true.

qrV2LowKBytesThreshold.name: qrV2LowKBytesThreshold
qrV2LowKBytesThreshold.description: A number of KBytes that when used by this entry produces a warning message. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This will return 0 if qrV2ThresholdUnlimited is true.

qrV2SoftQuotaUnlimited.name: qrV2SoftQuotaUnlimited
qrV2SoftQuotaUnlimited.description: This flag designates whether or not the size based soft quota limit for this qrV2Entry is unlimited. If false(1) then qrV2*KBytesSoftLimit OID's are valid, if true(0) the qrV2*KBytesSoftLimit OID's are unused and will return 0.

qrV2HighKBytesSoftLimit.name: qrV2HighKBytesSoftLimit
qrV2HighKBytesSoftLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrV2Entry before a warning message and SNMP trap is produced. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

qrV2LowKBytesSoftLimit.name: qrV2LowKBytesSoftLimit
qrV2LowKBytesSoftLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrV2Entry before a warning message and SNMP trap is produced. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

qrV2SoftFileQuotaUnlimited.name: qrV2SoftFileQuotaUnlimited
qrV2SoftFileQuotaUnlimited.description: This flag designates whether or not the file based soft quota limit for this qrV2Entry is unlimited. If false(1) then qrV2SoftFileLimit is valid, if true(0) qrV2SoftFileLimit is unused and will return 0.

qrV2SoftFileLimit.name: qrV2SoftFileLimit
qrV2SoftFileLimit.description: The limit of files that can be used for this qrV2Entry before a warning message and SNMP trap is produced. This will return 0 if qrV2SoftFileQuotaUnlimited is true.

qrV264KBytesUsed.name: qrV264KBytesUsed
qrV264KBytesUsed.description: The current number of KBytes used for this qrV2Entry. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

qrV264KBytesLimit.name: qrV264KBytesLimit
qrV264KBytesLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrV2Entry. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This will return 0 if qrV2QuotaUnlimited is true.

qrV264KBytesThreshold.name: qrV264KBytesThreshold
qrV264KBytesThreshold.description: A number of KBytes that when used by this entry produces a warning message. This object returns the all of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This will return 0 if qrV2ThresholdUnlimited is true.

qrV264KBytesSoftLimit.name: qrV264KBytesSoftLimit
qrV264KBytesSoftLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrV2Entry before a warning message and SNMP trap is produced. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

filesysMaxfilesAvail.name: filesysMaxfilesAvail
filesysMaxfilesAvail.description: The count of the maximum number of files allowable on the root volume. This object is deprecated - use dfEntry.dfMaxFilesAvail instead.

filesysMaxfilesUsed.name: filesysMaxfilesUsed
filesysMaxfilesUsed.description: The count of the number of files currently in use on the root volume. This object is deprecated - use dfEntry.dfMaxFilesUsed instead.

filesysMaxfilesPossible.name: filesysMaxfilesPossible
filesysMaxfilesPossible.description: The largest value to which the filesysMaxfilesAvail parameter above can be increased by reconfiguration on the root volume. This object is deprecated - use dfEntry.dfMaxFilesPossible.

dfTable.name: dfTable
dfTable.description: Provide a report of the available disk space on the file systems. The tables shows the available disk space for volumes as well as aggregates.

dfEntry.name: dfEntry
dfEntry.description: Provide a report of the available disk space on the referenced file system.

dfIndex.name: dfIndex
dfIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry for the referenced file system.

dfFileSys.name: dfFileSys
dfFileSys.description: The name for the referenced file system.

dfKBytesTotal.name: dfKBytesTotal
dfKBytesTotal.description: The total capacity in KBytes for the referenced file system.

dfKBytesUsed.name: dfKBytesUsed
dfKBytesUsed.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is in use on the referenced file system.

dfKBytesAvail.name: dfKBytesAvail
dfKBytesAvail.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is free for use on the referenced file system.

dfPerCentKBytesCapacity.name: dfPerCentKBytesCapacity
dfPerCentKBytesCapacity.description: The percentage of disk space currently in use on the referenced file system.

dfInodesUsed.name: dfInodesUsed
dfInodesUsed.description: The total number of inodes in use on the referenced file system.

dfInodesFree.name: dfInodesFree
dfInodesFree.description: The total number of inodes that are available for use on the referenced file system.

dfPerCentInodeCapacity.name: dfPerCentInodeCapacity
dfPerCentInodeCapacity.description: The percentage of disk space currently in use based on inode counts, on the referenced file system.

dfMountedOn.name: dfMountedOn
dfMountedOn.description: The name of the file on which this file system is mounted.

dfMaxFilesAvail.name: dfMaxFilesAvail
dfMaxFilesAvail.description: The count of the maximum number of files allowable on the referenced file system.

dfMaxFilesUsed.name: dfMaxFilesUsed
dfMaxFilesUsed.description: The count of the number of files currently in use on the referenced file system.

dfMaxFilesPossible.name: dfMaxFilesPossible
dfMaxFilesPossible.description: The largest value to which the filesysMaxfilesAvail parameter above can be increased by reconfiguration on the referenced file system.

dfHighTotalKBytes.name: dfHighTotalKBytes
dfHighTotalKBytes.description: The total capacity in KBytes for the referenced file system. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

dfLowTotalKBytes.name: dfLowTotalKBytes
dfLowTotalKBytes.description: The total capacity in KBytes for the referenced file system. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

dfHighUsedKBytes.name: dfHighUsedKBytes
dfHighUsedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is in use on the referenced file system. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

dfLowUsedKBytes.name: dfLowUsedKBytes
dfLowUsedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is in use on the referenced file system. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

dfHighAvailKBytes.name: dfHighAvailKBytes
dfHighAvailKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is free for use on the referenced file system. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

dfLowAvailKBytes.name: dfLowAvailKBytes
dfLowAvailKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is free for use on the referenced file system. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

dfStatus.name: dfStatus

dfMirrorStatus.name: dfMirrorStatus

dfPlexCount.name: dfPlexCount
dfPlexCount.description: Number of plexes in this file system.

dfHighSisSharedKBytes.name: dfHighSisSharedKBytes

dfLowSisSharedKBytes.name: dfLowSisSharedKBytes
dfLowSisSharedKBytes.description: The total amount of data in KBytes that is shared by more that one instance on the referenced file system. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

dfHighSisSavedKBytes.name: dfHighSisSavedKBytes
dfHighSisSavedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is saved by storing only one copy of the duplicated blocks on the referenced file system. The object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

dfLowSisSavedKBytes.name: dfLowSisSavedKBytes
dfLowSisSavedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is saved by storing only one copy of the duplicated blocks on the referenced file system. The object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

dfPerCentSaved.name: dfPerCentSaved
dfPerCentSaved.description: The percentage of disk space saved by eliminating the duplicated blocks on the referenced file system.

df64TotalKBytes.name: df64TotalKBytes
df64TotalKBytes.description: The total capacity in KBytes for the referenced file system. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

df64UsedKBytes.name: df64UsedKBytes
df64UsedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is in use on the referenced file system. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

df64AvailKBytes.name: df64AvailKBytes
df64AvailKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is free for use on the referenced file system. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

df64SisSharedKBytes.name: df64SisSharedKBytes
df64SisSharedKBytes.description: The total amount of data in KBytes that is shared by more that one instance on the referenced file system. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

df64SisSavedKBytes.name: df64SisSavedKBytes
df64SisSavedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is saved by storing only one copy of the duplicated blocks on the referenced file system. The object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

slTable.name: slTable

slEntry.description: Provide a report on a given snapshot on the root volume. This object is deprecated - use slVEntry instead.

slIndex.name: slIndex
slIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry for the referenced file system.

slMonth.name: slMonth
slMonth.description: The month in which the snapshot was created.

slDay.name: slDay

slHour.name: slHour
slHour.description: The hour in which the snapshot was created.

slMinutes.name: slMinutes
slMinutes.description: The minute in which the snapshot was created.

slName.name: slName

slVTable.name: slVTable
slVTable.description: Provide a report of the snapshots on the file systems.

slVEntry.name: slVEntry
slVEntry.description: Provide a report on a given snapshot on the file system. Indices select the volume of the snapshot and the snapshot entry itself.

slVIndex.name: slVIndex
slVIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry for the referenced file system.

slVMonth.name: slVMonth

slVDay.name: slVDay
slVDay.description: The day on which the snapshot was created.

slVHour.name: slVHour
slVHour.description: The hour in which the snapshot was created.

slVMinutes.name: slVMinutes

slVName.description: The name of the referenced snapshot.

slVNumber.name: slVNumber
slVNumber.description: Number of snapshots for this volume / aggregate.

slVVolumeName.name: slVVolumeName
slVVolumeName.description: The name of the volume / aggregate. This does not have a /vol/ prefix.

slVType.name: slVType
slVType.description: Indicates the type of container for this snapshot.

slQTable.description: Provide a report of the snapshots and their contents on the file systems.

slQSnapshotName.name: slQSnapshotName

slQQtreeName.name: slQQtreeName
slQQtreeName.description: A string that indicates which qtree is in this snapshot

slQQtreeContent.name: slQQtreeContent
slQQtreeContent.description: The content of the qtree tree

slQSource.name: slQSource
slQSource.description: The source of this qtree for a replicated qtree. '-' for a original qtree.

slQSourceTime.name: slQSourceTime
slQSourceTime.description: Time of the source snapshot for a replicated qtree. Time of the current snapshot for an original qtree. The time in seconds since January 1, 1970. 0 if the qtree is in a transitioning stage

slQVolumeName.name: slQVolumeName
slQVolumeName.description: The name of the volume. This does not have a /vol/ prefix.

dfNumber.name: dfNumber
dfNumber.description: Number of entries in the dfTable table.

fsOverallStatus.name: fsOverallStatus
fsOverallStatus.description: An indication of overall file system health. 'ok' indicates that all file systems have adequate space. 'nearlyFull' means that one or more is nearly full (more than 95% full). 'full' means that one or more are more than 98% full.

fsStatusMessage.name: fsStatusMessage
fsStatusMessage.description: A string indicating any file systems which are full or nearly full.

fsMaxUsedBytesPerCent.name: fsMaxUsedBytesPerCent
fsMaxUsedBytesPerCent.description: The percentage of space currently in use by the file system which is most full.

fsMaxUsedInodesPerCent.name: fsMaxUsedInodesPerCent
fsMaxUsedInodesPerCent.description: The percentage of inodes currently in use by the file system which is most full.

fsMaxUsedReservedPerCent.name: fsMaxUsedReservedPerCent
fsMaxUsedReservedPerCent.description: The percentage of reserved space currently in use by the file system which is most full.

volTable.name: volTable
volTable.description: List the volumes defined on the system, including offline volumes.

volEntry.name: volEntry
volEntry.description: Provide details about a particular volume.

volIndex.name: volIndex
volIndex.description: A number that identifies this volume. The volIndex is not related to any other table defined in this MIB, and may change as volumes are created and destroyed.

volName.name: volName
volName.description: Name of the volume. This includes no /vol/ prefix.

volOwningHost.name: volOwningHost
volOwningHost.description: Indication of which host owns this volume.

volState.name: volState
volState.description: State of the volume, such as 'online' or 'offline'.

volStatus.name: volStatus
volStatus.description: Status of the volume, such as 'normal' or 'reconstructing'. May include several values separated by comma and space.

volOptions.name: volOptions
volOptions.description: Options associated with the volume, such as 'root' and 'nosnapdir=off'. May include several values separated by comma.

volUUID.name: volUUID
volUUID.description: A unique id associated with the volume.

volAggrName.name: volAggrName
volAggrName.description: Name of the aggregate this flexible volume is a part of.

volType.name: volType
volType.description: Type of this volume, older volumes are traditional while newer volumes contained in aggregates are flexible.

volClone.name: volClone
volClone.description: True indicates flexible volume is a clone.

volCloneOf.name: volCloneOf
volCloneOf.description: Name of flexible volume this flexible volume is a clone of.

volNumber.name: volNumber
volNumber.description: Number of volumes in the volTable.

qtreeTable.name: qtreeTable
qtreeTable.description: Provide a list of the qtrees on the system.

qtreeEntry.name: qtreeEntry
qtreeEntry.description: Provide details about a particular qtree.

qtreeVolume.name: qtreeVolume
qtreeVolume.description: A number that identifies the volume that contains this qtree.

qtreeVolumeName.name: qtreeVolumeName
qtreeVolumeName.description: The name of the volume that contains this qtree. This includes no /vol/prefix.

qtreeId.name: qtreeId
qtreeId.description: The Id number of the qtree.

qtreeStyle.name: qtreeStyle
qtreeStyle.description: The security style of the qtree.

qtreeOplock.name: qtreeOplock
qtreeOplock.description: An indication of whether the oplocks is enabled or not for this qtree.

aggrTable.name: aggrTable
aggrTable.description: List the aggregates defined on the system, including offline aggregates.

aggrEntry.name: aggrEntry
aggrEntry.description: Provide details about a particular aggregate.

aggrIndex.name: aggrIndex
aggrIndex.description: A number that identifies this aggregate. The aggrIndex is not related to any other table defined in this MIB, and may change as aggregates are created and destroyed.

aggrName.name: aggrName
aggrName.description: Name of the aggregate. This includes no /vol/ prefix.

aggrOwningHost.name: aggrOwningHost
aggrOwningHost.description: Indication of which host owns this aggregate.

aggrState.name: aggrState
aggrState.description: State of the aggregate, such as 'online' or 'offline'.

aggrStatus.name: aggrStatus
aggrStatus.description: Status of the aggregate, such as 'normal' or 'reconstructing'. May include several values separated by comma and space.

aggrUUID.name: aggrUUID
aggrUUID.description: A unique id associated with the aggregate.

aggrFlexvollist.name: aggrFlexvollist
aggrFlexvollist.description: List of all the flexible volumes within this aggregate.

aggrType.name: aggrType
aggrType.description: Type of this container, containers containing flexible volumes are aggregate.

aggrRaidType.description: Type of raid protection of the aggregate, such as 'raid0', 'mirrored raid0', 'raid4', 'mirrored raid4', 'raid_dp', 'mirrored raid_dp'.

aggrNumber.name: aggrNumber
aggrNumber.description: Number of aggregates in the aggrTable.

For a dual-ported disk, values of portA and portB indicate which port is being used. raidVPlexName.description: A name that identifies the plex that this entry belongs to. A plex name can be anything, but is usually a string like 'plex0' or 'plex1'.

raidVSectorSize.description: A number that specifies bytes per sector for this entry. Values are '512' or '520'.

cifsIsEnabled.name: cifsIsEnabled
cifsIsEnabled.description: Whether the CIFS protocol is active on the filer.

cifsIsLoginEnabled.description: Whether new CIFS connections to the filer are currently allowed.

cifsHostName.description: The host name used by the CIFS protocol on this filer.

cifsAltNames.name: cifsAltNames
cifsAltNames.description: Alternate names recognized by the filer.

cifsDomainJoined.name: cifsDomainJoined
cifsDomainJoined.description: Has the filer joined an NT domain? If this value is true, cifsDomainName will contain the name of the domain. Otherwise, the filer may have joined a WorkGroup, and cifsWGName will contain the name of the WorkGroup.

cifsDomainName.name: cifsDomainName
cifsDomainName.description: The domain name used by the CIFS protocol on this filer.

cifsWGName.name: cifsWGName
cifsWGName.description: The workgroup name (if any) used by the CIFS protocol on this filer.

cifsDCName.name: cifsDCName
cifsDCName.description: The name of the Domain Controller used by this filer to authenticate users and file requests.

cifsIsWinsEnabled.name: cifsIsWinsEnabled
cifsIsWinsEnabled.description: True if WINS name resolution is enabled on the filer.

cifsWinsServers.name: cifsWinsServers
cifsWinsServers.description: The name(s) of the WINS servers registered with the filer.

cifsSecurityModel.name: cifsSecurityModel
cifsSecurityModel.description: Which type of authentication semantics (Unix or PC) are in use for PC access to Unix files on the filer. If Unix semantics are in use, no ACL on a Unix file is ever checked. If PC semantics are in use, the share level ACL on the share containing the file is used for authentication instead of the group portion of the permissions on the file.

cifsPCGenericUser.name: cifsPCGenericUser
cifsPCGenericUser.description: The name of the generic PC user, if any. This username is used for CIFS access by Unix users who have not authenticated through CIFS or NT.

cifsOplocksEnabled.name: cifsOplocksEnabled
cifsOplocksEnabled.description: Whether oplocks are enabled on the filer.

cifsLevel2OplocksEnabled.name: cifsLevel2OplocksEnabled
cifsLevel2OplocksEnabled.description: Whether level 2 oplocks are enabled on the filer.

cifsPreserveCase.name: cifsPreserveCase
cifsPreserveCase.description: If this option is set to preserve-case (the default), all filename references will be case preserving. Otherwise, they are forced to lowercase.

cifsSymlinksEnabled.name: cifsSymlinksEnabled
cifsSymlinksEnabled.description: If this option is enabled, CIFS accesses will follow symbolic links using Unix semantics.

cifsSymlinkCycleProtEnabled.name: cifsSymlinkCycleProtEnabled
cifsSymlinkCycleProtEnabled.description: If this option is enabled, CIFS accesses will through symbolic links will check for cycles in the link graph.

cifsIsLicensed.name: cifsIsLicensed

ncAdminPort.name: ncAdminPort
ncAdminPort.description: Netcache Admin Port number - this is the first in the list of admin ports configured for the NetCache.

amNumber.name: amNumber
amNumber.description: The number of entries in the acceleration monitor table.

amMonitor.name: amMonitor
amMonitor.description: Variable for user defined SNMP traps to monitor whether there has been a status change of any of the acceleration servers that netcache is probing.

amMonitorString.name: amMonitorString
amMonitorString.description: Used in conjunction with amMonitor. This returns a string in format of: 'IP:port status' which reports the status of all the servers netcache is accelerating as of last status change.

amTable.name: amTable
amTable.description: A list of acceleration server and port entries. The number of entries is given by the value of amNumber.

amEntry.name: amEntry
amEntry.description: An acceleration monitor entry contains: the server IP address, server port and the status.

amIndex.name: amIndex
amIndex.description: A unique value for each entry in the acceleration monitor table.

amAddress.name: amAddress
amAddress.description: The IP address of the acceleration server the NetCache is monitoring.

amPort.name: amPort
amPort.description: The corresponding port on the server that NetCache is monitoring.

amStatus.name: amStatus
amStatus.description: The status of the service running on the server. active - in queue but no probes done yet. up - the server is reachable and responding to probes. down - the server is unreachable. inactive - monitoring is disabled.

ncLocalConfigChanged.name: ncLocalConfigChanged
ncLocalConfigChanged.description: Whether the local configuration file on NetCache was changed without using DFM configuration management.

grmMonitorToggle.name: grmMonitorToggle
grmMonitorToggle.description: Variable for user defined SNMP traps to monitor whether there has been a status change of any of the GRM agents reporting to this GRM server.

grmMonitorString.name: grmMonitorString
grmMonitorString.description: Used in conjunction with grmMonitor. This returns a string in format of: 'IP status.' which reports the status of all the GRM agents reporting to this GRM server as of last status change.

takeoverAddrs.name: takeoverAddrs
takeoverAddrs.description: Indicates the list of interfaces and their corresponding IP addresses of the partner NetCache that this appliance has taken over.

takeoverMode.name: takeoverMode
takeoverMode.description: Indicates the current takeover mode of this appliance.

takeoverStatus.name: takeoverStatus
takeoverStatus.description: Indicates the current status of the takeover partner of this appliance. up(1) indicates that the takeover partner is reachable. unknown(2) indicates that an unknown error occured. failed(3) indicates that the partner has failed, takeoverAddrs indicates the partner's IP address this appliance has taken over.

dafsSessionNumRequests.name: dafsSessionNumRequests

dafsExportIndex.description: A unique value for each export. Its value ranges between 1 and the number of exports. The value for each export must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.

dafsExportName.name: dafsExportName
dafsExportName.description: A textual string containing information about the export. This is the logical export name.

dafsExportPath.name: dafsExportPath

dafsExportEnabled.name: dafsExportEnabled

viaCurrError.name: viaCurrError
viaCurrError.description: The number of VIs for which the current state is ERROR

viaTotalError.name: viaTotalError
viaTotalError.description: The number of VIs which encountered error state.

viaInMsgs.name: viaInMsgs
viaInMsgs.description: The total number of incoming Messages received.

viaInRdma.name: viaInRdma
viaInRdma.description: The total number of incoming RDMA requests received.

viaInBytes.name: viaInBytes
viaInBytes.description: The total number of incoming bytes received, including those received in error. This count includes bytes received on currently established connections. This corresponds to the sum of bytes received through received messages, incoming RDMA writes and RDMA reads issued

viaInRDMAReadBytes.name: viaInRDMAReadBytes
viaInRDMAReadBytes.description: The total number of incoming bytes received through RDMA read, including those received in error. This count includes bytes received on currently established connections.

viaInRDMAWriteBytes.name: viaInRDMAWriteBytes
viaInRDMAWriteBytes.description: The total number of bytes received through incoming RDMA writes, including those received in error. This count includes bytes received on currently established connections.

viaOutMsgs.name: viaOutMsgs
viaOutMsgs.description: The total number of Messages sent.

viaOutRdma.name: viaOutRdma
viaOutRdma.description: The total number of RDMA requests sent.

viaOutBytes.name: viaOutBytes
viaOutBytes.description: The total number of bytes sent, including those sent in error. This count includes bytes sent on currently established connections.

viaOutRDMAReadBytes.name: viaOutRDMAReadBytes

viaOutRDMAWriteBytes.name: viaOutRDMAWriteBytes
viaOutRDMAWriteBytes.description: The total number of bytes sent through a RDMA write operation, including those sent in error. This count includes bytes sent on currently established connections.

viaConnState.description: The state of this via connection Legal States: Idle 1 Pending Connect 2 Connected 3 Error 4

viaConnVINumber.name: viaConnVINumber
viaConnVINumber.description: A number which uniquely defines a connection.

viaConnRemoteNetAddress.name: viaConnRemoteNetAddress
viaConnRemoteNetAddress.description: IP address of the remote system of the connection.

viaConnRemotePortNumber.name: viaConnRemotePortNumber
viaConnRemotePortNumber.description: Remote TCP portnumber of the connection.

viaConnLocalPortNumber.name: viaConnLocalPortNumber
viaConnLocalPortNumber.description: Local TCP Portnumber of the connection.

viaConnLocalDescriminator.name: viaConnLocalDescriminator
viaConnLocalDescriminator.description: An identifier used by the local process to identify the VI connection.

viaConnRemoteDescriminator.name: viaConnRemoteDescriminator
viaConnRemoteDescriminator.description: An identifier used by the remote process to identify the VI connection.

viaConnRemoteMaxTransferSize.name: viaConnRemoteMaxTransferSize
viaConnRemoteMaxTransferSize.description: The remote limit on the maximum packet size that can be transfered through the connection.

viaConnLocalEnableRdmaWrite.description: The value is 1 if remote DMA write is enabled in the local system otherwise, it is 0.

viaConnLocalEnableRdmaRead.description: The value is 1 if remote DMA read is enabled in the local system otherwise, it is 0.

viaConnRemoteEnableRdmaWrite.name: viaConnRemoteEnableRdmaWrite

viaConnRemoteEnableRdmaRead.name: viaConnRemoteEnableRdmaRead
viaConnRemoteEnableRdmaRead.description: The value is 1 if remote DMA read is enabled in the remote system otherwise, it is 0.

viaConnRcvdRdmaReadMessages.name: viaConnRcvdRdmaReadMessages
viaConnRcvdRdmaReadMessages.description: Total number of rdma read messages received through the connection.

viaConnRcvdRdmaWriteMessages.name: viaConnRcvdRdmaWriteMessages
viaConnRcvdRdmaWriteMessages.description: Total number of rdma write messages received through the connection.

viaErrPostDesc.name: viaErrPostDesc
viaErrPostDesc.description: The total number of descriptors completed in error by NIC.

viaErrConnLost.name: viaErrConnLost

viaErrRecvQEmpty.name: viaErrRecvQEmpty

viaErrRdmarProt.name: viaErrRdmarProt
viaErrRdmarProt.description: The total number of remote DMA read protection errors.

viaErrCompProt.name: viaErrCompProt
viaErrCompProt.description: The total number of protection errors.
